<TITLE> Majority of readers reject Mujahid's claim: poll </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 29 (bdnews24.com)  An overwhelming majority of 82.30 percent of readers polled in a bdnews24.com online survey have dismissed the claim by Jamaat-e-Islami that there is no anti-liberation force or war criminal in the country. A total of 40,838 respondents participated in the survey posted Thursday after Jamaat's secretary general Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid made the claim at a meeting with the Election Commission. As many as 33,608 readers brushed aside Mujahid's claim until the close of the survey at 3:00pm Monday. Only 17.70 percent, or 7,230 respondents, agreed with Mujahid's claim. In a post-meeting news briefing, Mujahid repeated his claim, which was greeted with howls of protest and condemnation from freedom fighters, other political parties, civil society representatives and professional groups. Newspapers and television stations have run news reports and editorials on the issue, mainly condemning the statement by Mujahid, a minister during the latest political regime led by the BNP. b
